    "$comment": "Evaluation/calibration fixture for the semantic lexicon (vectors themselves come from pretrained GloVe embeddings — see scripts/fetch-embeddings.js). Roles: (1) vocab guarantee — every word in `concepts` and `extraWords` MUST have a GloVe vector; fetch-embeddings.js and build-lexicon.js both fail loudly if one doesn't. (2) related pairs for scripts/validate-lexicon.js — words in one cluster are synonyms/co-labels of a theme; clusters sharing a `parent` are siblings. Put the most canonical words FIRST in each cluster (the validator embeds the front of the list as the 'challenge title'). (3) `unrelatedParents` — parent pairs that are honestly unrelated in embedding space; the validator's noise distribution is built ONLY from concept pairs across these, because real embeddings legitimately relate e.g. vehicle<->urban. (4) `nearMissPairs` — concept-id pairs that are moderately related but wrong-theme (reported by the validator with a warning threshold, not gated). Words are stemmed at build time with the matcher's own stemmer; a stem collision between two clusters is a fatal authoring error, so check the build output after editing. Re-run `pnpm fetch:embeddings` (offline once the GloVe zip is cached) then `pnpm build:lexicon && pnpm verify:lexicon` after any edit.",
